<span class=title> For every loss there is a victory</span><hr size=1> Well I just found out about a neat thing on vox. Doing a CR and people fall in the pit here is a hint to everybody if you ever host vox raid. After raid if vox is alive or dead, if your a class that can cast invis, cast it on yourself. Then looking at middle ramp up to vox lair go right instead. You will fall in a pit, have the people consent you. Grab there corpses and find the latter. Go up the latter and i think another. And there you will see a narrow path going at a slant. Run up with it fast (good to have sow) you will pass a wooly spider, and two icy terrors. Just keep going forward. It looks like you hit a dead end but u will fall down and land in vox's lair. Then just run straight and you will run into a door. (i think its a door) or its a hole. Jump in and fall down like 2 feet. Then u will fall down again and land in the ''king room'' you wont have adds chaising you. And vox wont summon you because of you didn't hit her. If you hit her if she is up. Well thats a helpful hint. Good Luck people. BTW HAPPY HALOWEEN <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lanhorn>Lanhorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 4:36:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverndragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1289.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm</span><hr size=1> thanks cliff I never understood the pit well...<br>
